## Available Tools

| Tool                      | Description                                             |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| `jira_get_issue`          | Get details of a specific Jira issue (e.g., `PROJ-123`) |
| `jira_search`             | Search Jira issues using JQL                            |
| `jira_get_project_issues` | Get all issues for a specific Jira project              |

## Available Resources

- `jira://{project_key}` - Access Jira project and its issues
- `jira://{project_key}/issues/{issue_key}` - Access specific Jira issues

## Usage Examples

```json
// Get project issues
{
  "project_key": "KAN",
  "limit": 10
}

// Search issues
{
  "jql": "project = KAN AND status = 'To Do'",
  "limit": 10
}

// Get specific issue
{
  "issue_key": "KAN-1"
}
```

## Configuration

The server uses environment variables for authentication:

- `JIRA_URL` - Atlassian instance URL
- `JIRA_USERNAME` - Email address for authentication
- `JIRA_API_TOKEN` - API token from https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens

## Notes

- The server is installed as an editable Python package (`pip install -e`)
- Python 3.12 is used as the runtime
- The server runs via stdio transport
